ays\n|\nIt is not an easy thing to be a woman and love with the whole heart: which men do not understand -- having many loves, and delighting in danger and war.\n\n- M.M.\n|\nBook collecting is a full-time occupation, and one wouldn't get far if one took time off for frivolities like reading.\n\n- A.N.L.\n|\nWhen a character comes to life, it’s like meeting a new friend for the first time.\n\n- Lynette\n|\nCrafty men condemn studies; Simple men admire them; And wise men use them: For they teach not their own use: but that is a wisdom without them, and above them, won by observation.\n\n- Francis\n|\nI couldn’t quite believe how much I seriously loved Aled Last, even if it wasn’t in the ideal way that would make it socially acceptable for us to live together until we die.\n\n- Alice Oseman, Radio Silence\n|\nMany people in life will catch your eye, but few will catch your heart. Make sure you notice the difference.\n\n- Lorri\n|\nIf you believe in Christ Jesus, you shall not perish but have everlasting life.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nLove is cure, love is power,love is magicof changes,love is the mirror of divine beauty\n\n- Altaf\n|\nSometimes small things can become very large, indeed.\n\n- Rick\n|\nI Am In Love With Myself, With My Heart.\n\n- Nirav\n|\nMan has made remarkable strides in conquering outer space, but how futile have been his efforts in conquering inner space- the space in our hearts and minds of men.\n\n- Thomas\n|\nStrip back the beliefs pasted on by governesses, schools, and states, you find indelible truths at one's core.\n\n- David\n|\nI was not alone in my success, only in my failure.\n\n- J. Devau, Theory of the Atheist: Record One of the Alias Wars\n|\nOn this day, take time to remember those who have fallen. But on every day after, do more; put the freedoms they died for to greater and nobler uses.\n\n- Richelle E. Goodrich, Slaying Dragons\n|\nDraw a circle, not a heart, around the one you love because a heart can break but a circle goes on forever.\